The Senate Foreign Relations Committee endorsed the nomination of Republican
activist Peter Secchia to be ambassador to Italy.  The chairman, Senator
Pell, had many misgivings about the nomination but did not vote against
Secchia.  Secchia pledged to be more careful in his use of language as a
diplomat that he had used as an activist.  Pell was not convinced.  He said
that the nomination was a mistake and that "in all likelihood Mr. Secchia
will be an embarrassment to the administration and the United States".
However, since Secchia is the president's choice he would not try to block
it.</SUM>

<SUM
