SUMMARIZER="F">

President Bush plans to name UN Ambassador Thomas Pickering as US envoy to
India and to appoint Foreign Service Director General Edward Perkins to
replace him.  The long, bitter feud between India and Pakistan, now both
nuclear powers, means Pickering's new job could be important.  Pickering's
posting to the UN was one of Bush's first appointments and his service there
covered the time when negotiations were underway to form he coalition
against Iraq in the Gulf War. Mr. Perkins was ambassador to South Africa
when the US imposed economic sanctions against that nation's white-minority
government to pressure it to end apartheid.</SUM>

<SUM
